Actually... ZeroTalk is capable to become a multi-language board. I just created [a sub-board for ZeroNet dev](/Talk.ZeroNetwork.bit/?Topics:9_1AWwhg4EiWAVttfQboJZ4wJfX3WawfJT3h/ZeroNet+Dev+Board). The problem is that ZeroTalk doesn't have merger-hub feature, and the site can grow too big if it allows other languages. And when the zite grows too big, it will take too much time to load and syn.
So we just need to create a better guide for other language speakers, like what is suggested from [this topic](/Talk.ZeroNetwork.bit/?Topic:13_13aB79mzuRLgDYzQthn9wzycjw77WyDXh6/Nofish+it+is+time+to+take+action+for+Chinese+posts), or use [the filter I created](/Talk.ZeroNetwork.bit/?Topic:8_1AWwhg4EiWAVttfQboJZ4wJfX3WawfJT3h), or create a better official Reddit-like zite like [ZeroVoat](/1J1c7eML6uMwDU4uiKbKRxoqxGP6WMFMvb/)

